Traditional medicinal uses are numerous, and many are shared with other 
 Momordica spp. In East and Central Africa, 
 M. foetida extracts are used to treat hypertension, peptic ulcers, and diabetes. Foetidin isolated from 
 M. foetida is capable of reducing blood-glucose level in fasting albino rats (
 Marquis et al., 1977). Likewise, 
 M. foetida is used for treatment of digestive problems due to its hypoglycemic activity that reduces the amount of sugar in the blood and also stimulate appetite and helps in the entire digestion process (
 Leung et al., 2009; 
 Kumar and Bhowmik, 2010; 
 Chen et al., 2011; 
 Daniel et al., 2014; 
 Birla, 2016).
